als, one shy of tying Jenny Thompson for most ever by a female swimmer and two shy of matching the all-time record for gold medals by a female Olympian.\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1167, \"end\": 1181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jenny Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 1288, \"end\": 1296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999998960929642, \"rank\": 1.0390723834908816e-07, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1099}, {\"ngram\": \"the Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1127}, {\"ngram\": \"six gold medals\", \"from\": 1133, \"to\": 1148}, {\"ngram\": \"a female swimmer\", \"from\": 1199, \"to\": 1215}, {\"ngram\": \"the all-time record\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1259}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medals\", \"from\": 1264, \"to\": 1275}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She's gone back and forth with Titmus over the years.\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1330, \"end\": 1336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the years\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1351}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Ledecky has the Olympic record in the 400-meter freestyle with a 3:56.46, set at the 2016 Games, Titmus took home the gold in Tokyo and currently holds the world record with a 3:55.38.\", \"from\": 1353